## Coding Conventions

### TypeScript
- Strict mode always. No `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow with type guards.
- All Supabase queries use the generated types from `supabase gen types typescript`
- Domain metadata typed with discriminated unions, not loose `jsonb`

### Components
- Functional components only. No class components.
- One component per file. File name = component name.
- Props always typed with an interface, e.g. `interface EntryCardProps { ... }`

### State
- Local UI state: `useState` / `useReducer`
- Server state: custom hooks (`useEntries`, `useBriefing`) that wrap Supabase queries
- No Redux, no Zustand for MVP — keep it simple

### Error handling
- Every async function has try/catch
- Errors surface to user via toast notification (expo-toast or react-native-toast)
- Never silently swallow errors

### Naming
- Hooks: `useXxx` (e.g. `useEntries`, `useBriefing`)
- Screens: `XxxScreen` (e.g. `TasksScreen`, `HealthScreen`)
- Cards/list items: `XxxCard` (e.g. `EntryCard`, `LearningCard`)
- Edge functions: kebab-case directories (e.g. `classify-entry/`, `morning-briefing/`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g. `DOMAINS`, `MODEL_MAP`)

### Domain constants (always use this, never hardcode strings)
```typescript
// constants/domains.ts
export const DOMAINS = {
  HEALTH:   'health',
  TASK:     'task',
  LEARNING: 'learning',
  IDEA:     'idea',
  NOTE:     'note',
} as const

export type Domain = typeof DOMAINS[keyof typeof DOMAINS]
```

### Offline-first pattern
- Read: expo-sqlite first → render optimistically → sync Supabase in background
- Write: expo-sqlite immediately (optimistic) → Supabase in background
- Conflict resolution: last-write-wins (acceptable for single-user personal app)

### Git
- Commit messages imperative: "Add voice input component" not "Added voice input"
- Never commit .env, node_modules, .expo, or generated Supabase types (add to .gitignore)
- Branch per feature: `feature/voice-input`, `feature/health-reminders`

